results.name: Square array T(n,k), n>=1, k>=1, read by antidiagonals in which column k lists the positive integers whose number of divisors is not k.
comment: Column k lists the numbers j such that A000005(j) <> k.
example: Column 2 lists the nonprimes A018252 because they are the positive integers whose number of divisors is not 2.
results.author: _Omar E. Pol_, Aug 11 2012
